result.name: Chao Inn

reviews.text: Awful food. Awful service. Totally NOT recommended. Overpriced kack
Food are nice but quite expensive. Staff is not friendly especially staff stand on front desk. We pay for our food but her voice like we owe her money..

Horrible, horrible restaurant. Extremely overpriced- it cost me 42 USD for two people, and that was with the cheap foods. They messed up my girlfriend's order even when she very specifically pointed out what she wanted. It took an hour for them to fix it and get her the right thing. The staff (consisting of several people) paid us almost no attention at all. It was very difficult to get service from them and it was very obvious that they were bringing out orders for people who got there after us first. I had a suspicion that the place does not like foreigners. Please, for your sake, stay away from this place at all costs.

The place had mediocre dim sum. On the way out at the counter when we had a couple questions about the prices for the things we ordered--didn't read the fine print (tea, a whopping 13 HKD per person, and a service charge of 13%). As we asked what the charges were since everything was in Chinese, the cashier working at 8 p.m. impatiently said in Cantonese that we didn't have money--thinking we didn't understand....which was not the point of us asking. We just didn't want to get charged for something we didn't order....Food also took at least 25 minutes to come out and one of our orders got mixed up.
Put it this way, it didn't suck even when this is an airport restaurant. Chiuchow style dishes are actually good enough for recommendations.
